## <span class="mw-headline" id="Introduction">Introduction</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span>[edit](/wiki/index.php?title=10_Segment_LED_Bar_Graph_(SKU:FIT0188)&veaction=edit&vesection=1 "Edit section: Introduction") <span class="mw-editsection-divider">|</span> [edit source](/wiki/index.php?title=10_Segment_LED_Bar_Graph_(SKU:FIT0188)&action=edit&section=1 "Edit section: Introduction")<span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span>

These 10 segment bar graph LEDs have many uses. With a compact footprint, and a simple hookup, they are easy for prototyping or finished products. Essentially, they are 10 individual red LEDs housed together.

### <span class="mw-headline" id="Applications">Applications</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span>[edit](/wiki/index.php?title=10_Segment_LED_Bar_Graph_(SKU:FIT0188)&veaction=edit&vesection=2 "Edit section: Applications") <span class="mw-editsection-divider">|</span> [edit source](/wiki/index.php?title=10_Segment_LED_Bar_Graph_(SKU:FIT0188)&action=edit&section=2 "Edit section: Applications")<span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span>

*   Audio equipment
*   Instrument panels
*   Digital readout display
*   Signal strength display
*   Power status display
*   Art display

### <span class="mw-headline" id="Specification">Specification</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span>[edit](/wiki/index.php?title=10_Segment_LED_Bar_Graph_(SKU:FIT0188)&veaction=edit&vesection=3 "Edit section: Specification") <span class="mw-editsection-divider">|</span> [edit source](/wiki/index.php?title=10_Segment_LED_Bar_Graph_(SKU:FIT0188)&action=edit&section=3 "Edit section: Specification")<span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span>

*   Forward Current (Per Segment): 25mA
*   Max Reverse Voltage: 5v
*   10 segment bar
*   Color: Super Bright Red
*   Industrial standard size
*   Low power consumption
*   Categorized for luminous intensity

### <span class="mw-headline" id="Shipping_List">Shipping List</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span>[edit](/wiki/index.php?title=10_Segment_LED_Bar_Graph_(SKU:FIT0188)&veaction=edit&vesection=4 "Edit section: Shipping List") <span class="mw-editsection-divider">|</span> [edit source](/wiki/index.php?title=10_Segment_LED_Bar_Graph_(SKU:FIT0188)&action=edit&section=4 "Edit section: Shipping List")<span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span>

*   10 segment led bar graph - Red (1 unit)

## <span class="mw-headline" id="Connection_Diagram">Connection Diagram</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span>[edit](/wiki/index.php?title=10_Segment_LED_Bar_Graph_(SKU:FIT0188)&veaction=edit&vesection=5 "Edit section: Connection Diagram") <span class="mw-editsection-divider">|</span> [edit source](/wiki/index.php?title=10_Segment_LED_Bar_Graph_(SKU:FIT0188)&action=edit&section=5 "Edit section: Connection Diagram")<span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span>

<div class="center">

<div class="thumb tnone">

<div class="thumbinner" style="width:702px;">[![](/wiki/images/thumb/e/e5/FIT0188_Connection.png/700px-FIT0188_Connection.png)](/wiki/index.php/File:FIT0188_Connection.png)

<div class="thumbcaption">

<div class="magnify">[](/wiki/index.php/File:FIT0188_Connection.png "Enlarge")</div>

10 Segment LED Bar Graph Connection</div>

</div>

</div>

</div>

Please note that the connection diagram shows the pins connected in reverse order for the sake of clarity. When you run the sample code included here you might notice a reverse order sequence. If you wish to wire the LEDs in the correct order you should wire:
Arduino D2 to PIN1
Arduino D3 to PIN2
Arduino D4 to PIN3
Arduino D5 to PIN4
and so on...

Alternatively you could modify the sample code to operate in the expected order.

## <span class="mw-headline" id="Sample_Code">Sample Code</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span>[edit](/wiki/index.php?title=10_Segment_LED_Bar_Graph_(SKU:FIT0188)&veaction=edit&vesection=6 "Edit section: Sample Code") <span class="mw-editsection-divider">|</span> [edit source](/wiki/index.php?title=10_Segment_LED_Bar_Graph_(SKU:FIT0188)&action=edit&section=6 "Edit section: Sample Code")<span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span>

<div class="mw-highlight mw-content-ltr" dir="ltr">

<pre><span class="c1">// #</span> 
<span class="c1">// # Editor     : Lauren from DFRobot</span>
<span class="c1">// # Date       : 19.03.2012</span>

<span class="c1">// # Product name: 10 Segment LED Bar Graph</span>
<span class="c1">// # Product SKU : FIT0188</span>
<span class="c1">// # Version     : 1.0</span>

<span class="c1">// # Description:</span>
<span class="c1">// # The sketch for using the 10 Segment LED Bar Graph with prototype shield</span>

<span class="c1">// # Connection:</span>
<span class="c1">// #        LED Bar positive pins -- Arduino digital pins through a 1K resistor</span>
<span class="c1">// #        LED Bar negative pins -- GND</span>

<span class="k">const</span> <span class="kt">int</span> <span class="n">ledPin</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="mi">10</span><span class="p">]</span> <span class="o">=</span>  <span class="p">{</span>
  <span class="mi">2</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="mi">3</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="mi">4</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="mi">5</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="mi">6</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="mi">9</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="mi">10</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="mi">11</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="mi">12</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="mi">13</span><span class="p">};</span>      <span class="c1">// the number of the LED pins</span>
<span class="kt">int</span> <span class="n">ledState</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="mi">0</span><span class="p">;</span>

<span class="kt">void</span> <span class="nf">setup</span><span class="p">()</span> <span class="p">{</span>
  <span class="n">Serial</span><span class="p">.</span><span class="n">begin</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="mi">9600</span><span class="p">);</span>
  <span class="c1">// set the digital pin as output:</span>
  <span class="k">for</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="kt">int</span> <span class="n">i</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="mi">0</span><span class="p">;</span> <span class="n">i</span> <span class="o"><</span> <span class="mi">10</span> <span class="p">;</span><span class="n">i</span> <span class="o">++</span><span class="p">){</span>
    <span class="n">pinMode</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">ledPin</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="n">i</span><span class="p">],</span> <span class="n">OUTPUT</span><span class="p">);</span>
    <span class="n">digitalWrite</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">ledPin</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="n">i</span><span class="p">],</span> <span class="n">LOW</span><span class="p">);</span>    
  <span class="p">}</span>
  <span class="n">ledState</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="mi">1</span><span class="p">;</span>
  <span class="n">display</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">ledState</span><span class="p">);</span>
  <span class="n">delay</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="mi">100</span><span class="p">);</span>
<span class="p">}</span>

<span class="kt">void</span> <span class="nf">loop</span><span class="p">()</span>
<span class="p">{</span> 
  <span class="k">for</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="kt">int</span> <span class="n">i</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="mi">0</span><span class="p">;</span> <span class="n">i</span> <span class="o"><</span> <span class="mi">9</span><span class="p">;</span> <span class="n">i</span><span class="o">++</span><span class="p">){</span>
    <span class="n">ledState</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">ledState</span> <span class="o"><<</span> <span class="mi">1</span><span class="p">;</span>
    <span class="n">display</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">ledState</span><span class="p">);</span>
    <span class="n">delay</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="mi">50</span><span class="p">);</span>
    <span class="n">Serial</span><span class="p">.</span><span class="n">println</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">ledState</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="n">BIN</span><span class="p">);</span>
  <span class="p">}</span>
  <span class="k">for</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="kt">int</span> <span class="n">i</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="mi">9</span><span class="p">;</span> <span class="n">i</span> <span class="o">></span> <span class="mi">0</span><span class="p">;</span> <span class="n">i</span><span class="o">--</span><span class="p">){</span>
    <span class="n">ledState</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">ledState</span> <span class="o">>></span> <span class="mi">1</span><span class="p">;</span>
    <span class="n">display</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">ledState</span><span class="p">);</span>
    <span class="n">delay</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="mi">50</span><span class="p">);</span>
    <span class="n">Serial</span><span class="p">.</span><span class="n">println</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">ledState</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="n">BIN</span><span class="p">);</span>
  <span class="p">}</span>
<span class="p">}</span>

<span class="kt">void</span> <span class="nf">display</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="kt">int</span> <span class="n">sat</span><span class="p">){</span>
  <span class="k">for</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="kt">int</span> <span class="n">i</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="mi">0</span><span class="p">;</span> <span class="n">i</span> <span class="o"><</span> <span class="mi">10</span> <span class="p">;</span><span class="n">i</span> <span class="o">++</span><span class="p">){</span>
    <span class="n">digitalWrite</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">ledPin</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="n">i</span><span class="p">],</span><span class="n">bitRead</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">ledState</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="n">i</span><span class="p">));</span>
  <span class="p">}</span>
<span class="p">}</span>
</pre>

</div>

